cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Japan Construction Cost Database: An Open Dataset for LLM-Based Cost Estimation and Fraud Detection in Residential Renovation"
abstract: >-
  An open, machine-readable structured dataset linking residential
  construction plan-level pricing, contractor-size-tier margin ranges,
  and fraud-detection patterns for the Japanese market. JCCDB v1.1
  comprises 87 construction plans across 7 renovation categories,
  annotated with 88 fraud-detection patterns categorized by severity.
  Pricing is derived from the HORIZON SHIELD (HS) Rule, a transparent
  cost formula grounded in 30 years of hands-on construction management
  practice combined with 2026 Kanto-region trade-price data. Each plan
  is stratified across four contractor-size tiers, with margin ranges
  drawn from Ministry of Land, Infrastructure, Transport and Tourism
  (MLIT) industry analysis. Released under CC-BY 4.0 to support
  NLP/LLM research on Japanese construction cost estimation,
  consumer-protection studies, and cross-country comparative analysis.
